<!DOCTYPE topic SYSTEM "mingle_help.dtd">
<topic title="Uninstalling Mingle">
	
	<section title="How to uninstall Mingle from Windows" collapsed="true">
		<steps>
			<item><p>Double-click the Mingle uninstaller file and follow the prompts to uninstall Mingle. Click 'Next' to continue.</p>
				<screenshot alttext="Uninstall Mingle" src="resources/images/uninstall_begin.png" />
			</item>	
			<item><p>Mingle will remove relevant Mingle files <strong>except</strong> the following:</p>
				  <bullets>
					<item>The data directory and database</item>
					<item>The activemq-data directory</item>
					<item>The tmp directory - contains cache, project import/export information</item>
					<item>The log directory - contains all mingle log files</item>
					<item>The public directory - contains any custom plugin files (if there are any)</item>
				  </bullets>
				<screenshot alttext="Uninstall Mingle" src="resources/images/uninstall_progress.png" />
			</item>
			<item><p>Mingle is successfully uninstalled.</p>  
				<screenshot alttext="Uninstall Mingle" src="resources/images/uninstall_complete.png" />
			</item>
		</steps>

	</section>

  <section title="How to uninstall Mingle from Linux/Unix/Mac OSX" collapsed="true">
    <steps>
      <item><p>Stop Mingle server. From the Mingle installation directory, type:</p>
        <markup>./MingleServer stop</markup>
      </item>
      <item>Remove any data that may be associated with the Mingle instance.</item>
    </steps>
  </section>

	<section title="Also see...">
